ğŸ§  What is Routing?

Routing means:
ğŸ‘‰ Showing different components based on the URL.

Example:

* `/` â†’ Home
* `/about` â†’ About Page
* `/contact` â†’ Contact Page

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸŒ What is React Router?

React Router is a library used to:

* Handle navigation in React apps
* Create Single Page Applications (SPA)
* Change UI without reloading page

ğŸ“Œ Most used library: `react-router-dom`

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Step 1: Install React Router

```bash
npm install react-router-dom
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Step 2: Setup BrowserRouter

Wrap your app with `BrowserRouter`.

```jsx
import { BrowserRouter } from "react-router-dom";

function App() {
  return (
    <BrowserRouter>
      <Home />
    </BrowserRouter>
  );
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Usually done in `main.jsx` or `index.js`

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Step 3: Define Routes

```jsx
import { Routes, Route } from "react-router-dom";

function App() {
  return (
    <BrowserRouter>
      <Routes>
        <Route path="/" element={<Home />} />
        <Route path="/about" element={<About />} />
        <Route path="/contact" element={<Contact />} />
      </Routes>
    </BrowserRouter>
  );
}
```

ğŸ“Œ `path` â†’ URL
ğŸ“Œ `element` â†’ Component to render

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Step 4: Navigation using Link

```jsx
import { Link } from "react-router-dom";

function Navbar() {
  return (
    <nav>
      <Link to="/">Home</Link>
      <Link to="/about">About</Link>
      <Link to="/contact">Contact</Link>
    </nav>
  );
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Avoid `<a>` tag
ğŸ“Œ Use `<Link>` for SPA navigation

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Navigation using useNavigate

```jsx
import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom";

function Login() {
  const navigate = useNavigate();

  const handleLogin = () => {
    navigate("/dashboard");
  };

  return <button onClick={handleLogin}>Login</button>;
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Used for programmatic navigation

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Dynamic Routing (Very Important â­)

Dynamic routes use URL parameters.

```jsx
<Route path="/user/:id" element={<User />} />
```

Access parameter:

```jsx
import { useParams } from "react-router-dom";

function User() {
  const { id } = useParams();
  return <h2>User ID: {id}</h2>;
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Useful for:

* Product pages
* User profiles
* Blog posts

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Nested Routes

```jsx
<Route path="/dashboard" element={<Dashboard />}>
  <Route path="profile" element={<Profile />} />
  <Route path="settings" element={<Settings />} />
</Route>
```

ğŸ“Œ Use `<Outlet />` inside parent component.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· 404 Page (Not Found)

```jsx
<Route path="*" element={<NotFound />} />
```

ğŸ“Œ Handles invalid routes

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· React Router Components Summary

| Component     | Purpose                 |
| ------------- | ----------------------- |
| BrowserRouter | Wrap entire app         |
| Routes        | Group routes            |
| Route         | Define route            |
| Link          | Navigation              |
| useNavigate   | Programmatic navigation |
| useParams     | Access URL params       |
| Outlet        | Nested routes           |

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  SPA (Single Page Application)

In SPA:

* Page doesnâ€™t reload
* Only components change
* Faster experience
* Better UX

React Router helps build SPA.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âš ï¸ Common Mistakes

âŒ Using `<a>` instead of `<Link>`
âŒ Forgetting BrowserRouter
âŒ Wrong path syntax
âŒ Not handling 404 page

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ’¡ Best Practices

âœ” Keep routes organized
âœ” Use separate route files
âœ” Use layout components
âœ” Handle 404 page
âœ” Use dynamic routing properly

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  Real-World Use Cases

* Multi-page portfolio
* Dashboard apps
* E-commerce websites
* Blog applications
* Admin panels

